^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, let's talk a little about gambling 3N. Some people play that you open 3N with a long running minor suit. The classic gambling 3N is with an 8 card minor with at least the top 3 honors. Some people also feel you should have no outside Aces. Kerrie did not really have a classic gambling 3N. She only had a 7 card minor. It was a reasonable gamble that it would take 7 tricks, even without the Jack of clubs. Because as long as I have at least 1 club, she is odds-on favorite to take 7 tricks. However, I was just informed that some people play 7 to the AKQJ is okay for gambling as well. Click |CP|1|at|^*GNOM,here^*N|CP||AT| to read more on gambling 3NT. You can return here afterwards.|
PG| ***** 14 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Anyway, as usual, I am not quite as disciplined. I play it does show a long minor, and an 8 trick hand but that is it. You could have 8 solid in the minor or 7 solid and an outside Ace or even 8 solid and an outside Ace. I think trying to make it disciplined is a bit silly. You are either a "gambler" or you are not. Basically you are betting that 3N is the right place and that more often than not you will be right.|
