NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, it turns out they are cold for six, due to their double fit in hearts and diamonds. Let's use Bergen Points to see if it makes sense to bid it. Kerrie has 11 Bergen Points--just her HCP. In fact, one could argue she should deduct a point for her 4-3-3-3 shape. East has 17 Starting Points: 16 HCP, two length points (one for each 5 card suit), one 1 for quality hearts, minus two for singleton King and Jx. Once Kerrie raises, East can then add 2 for the singleton and 1 for the side diamond suit. That gives her 20. Since Kerrie has at most 12, slam is a bit remote.|
PG| ***** 70 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|But, because Kerrie has the perfect cards, slam happens to make. Change any of her high cards to somewhere else (for example make the A of clubs the A of spades) and slam has no plays. I do not think slam should be bid. Further, you cannot bid slam unless you play a sophisticated bidding system with what are known as "asking bids."|
