ub||mb|4c|NT|^B@2
4C Shows weakness and indicates a desire to play in opener's long Minor suit. The opener either passes if the long minor suit was Clubs or corrects to 4D with South's hand.|
PG| ***** 163 ***** |


uB||mb|4d|NT|^B@2
4D is an artificial bid, asking for a singleton. 
1. If opener has a singleton in a Major suit, the opener bids that suit. A 4H rebid shows a singleton in Hearts and a 4S rebid shows a singleton in Spades. 
2. If opener bids 4NT, this shows a singleton in either of the Minor suits. 
3. If opener bids 5C or 5D, then opener has a singleton in other Minor suit and the bid establishes the long, solid Minor suit. |
